text segment ground truth by labelling answer spans returned by the count extractor [roy2015reasoning] as positive when the count lies within {{arxiv_2209_07250_FO0029||FO}} from the ground truth. 
There are around 800 queries with no positive snippets, which we do not discard, so the system is not forced to generate an answer. In the end we have {{arxiv_2209_07250_FO0030||FO}} count queries with automated ground truth, and an average of {{arxiv_2209_07250_FO0031||FO}} annotated text segments per query.